## Coding Standards

Follow these dedicated rule files (do not duplicate conflicting patterns here):

| Concern | Rule file |
|---------|-----------|
| Layers & dependency rule | `clean_architecture.mdc` |
| Feature folders | `feature_organization.mdc` |
| BLoC + freezed + Either | `state_management.mdc` |
| Failures / Dartz | `error_handling.mdc` |
| Use cases & repositories | `use_case_pattern.mdc` / `repository_pattern.mdc` |
| GetIt registration | `dependency_injection.mdc` |
| Named routes | `routing.mdc` |
| l10n / ARB | `localization.mdc` |
| GScaffold, GText, theme | `ui_guidelines.mdc` |
| Tests / performance / quality | `testing.mdc`, `performance.mdc`, `code_quality.mdc` |
| Feature README | `readme_structure.mdc` |

### Hard requirements (always)
- Prefer Dartz `Either<Failure, T>` for use-case and repository results — never `DataSuccess` / `DataFailed`
- Register BLoCs with `registerFactory` only (never `registerSingleton` for BLoCs)
- Use domain entities in presentation; map DTOs → entities in the data layer
- No hardcoded UI strings; use `AppLocalizations`
- No raw `Scaffold` / ad-hoc colors; use `GScaffold`, `GText`, `GButton`, and `app_theme`
